<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Face it people! There isnt a large market for PVP. I enjoy PVP very much. These large uber guilds of elite players will very much exist in Shadowbane.<P>You think EQ has a bunch of lifeless drones on the leveling treadmill? Wait till SB comes out. Its gonna take far more dedication and time. The elite losers will flock there. People with nothing better to do with their time. People who will live and sleep SB. You don’t think so? Your kingdom will fall quickly unless you have 24/7 support, plain and simple.<P>You ever see the web sites for uber guilds in EQ?  You MUST be 60. You MUST spend at least 8 hours a day online. You MUST have all your spells. You MUST have the best equipment. What makes you think SB will be any different?  Try running a kingdom with a guild filled with casual players. Limited PVP and alot of PVE content is key to the success of a MMORPG. The masses cant dedicate the time it will take to run a kingdom and the guilds who want the best kingdom will be uber.  Yeah, Sounds like fun. <P>SB- Spend 1 to 2 hours a day. (Still a decent amount of dedication) after about 6 months everything you built destroyed by a 8 hour a day uber guild. Start it all over again only to be crushed again.<P>Point: Unless your planning on dedicating your life to SB you will be crushed by the uber guilds and grow frustrated very quickly of logging in only to be killed constantly. Uber guilds with the power to kill you whenever they want will make most people quit. Look at UO! They had the freedom of killing whoever, whenever. They saw this was becoming a big problem and modified their game.<P>EQ- Dedication pays off with rewards. Rewards that cannot be taken by anyone. The frustration with EQ is the uber guilds take all the spawns and named mobs. You have a MUCH better chance of being successful in EQ than you do in SB.<P>This is one reason why EQ is and will continue to be a great success.<P><BR>For the record I love the idea of SB. I just don’t think I have enough time to play it. I also don’t think I will find myself on the winning “Team” without giving myself to them 100%	<P>Disagree?  Lets hear your thoughts...
